						               													<description>This very simple game is for children of 3 years and older and is designed to teach color recognition. Each player has an empty pole and six wooden beads in the colors red, blue, green, yellow, orange and purple. On their turn the player throws a color die, and if they do not already have a bead of the color thrown then they place one on their pole. The winner is the first player to have collected a set of beads of all six colors. In a variant game, the beads are all placed in groups on the board, which shows a multi-colored worm. The beads must be placed on a player's pole in the same order in which they appear on the worm.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Similar to:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Rainbow Towers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
